  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I open a Snapchat video that won't let me open?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble opening a Snapchat video, you can try the following troubleshooting steps:\n\n1. **Restart the App**:\n   - Close the Snapchat app entirely and reopen it to see if the problem resolves itself.\n\n2. **Check Your Internet Connection**:\n   - Ensure you have a stable internet connection, either via Wi-Fi or mobile data. Unstable connections can cause videos not to load.\n\n3. **Restart Your Device**:\n   - Sometimes, simply restarting your device can resolve temporary glitches.\n\n4. **Clear Cache (for Android Devices)**:\n   - Go to your device's settings > Apps > Snapchat > Storage > Clear Cache. This won't delete your account or snaps but can help fix loading issues.\n\n5. **Update the App**:\n   - Make sure you have the latest version of Snapchat installed. Update the app via the App Store (iOS) or Google Play Store (Android).\n\n6. **Check for App Permissions**:\n   - Ensure that Snapchat has the necessary permissions to access storage and other necessary settings on your device.\n\n7. **Reinstall the App**:\n   - If the problem persists, uninstall Snapchat and then reinstall it from the App Store or Google Play Store.\n\n8. **Free Up Space**:\n   - Ensure your device has enough storage available. A lack of storage can cause media to fail to load or open.\n\n9. **Check for Snapchat Outages**:\n   - Sometimes, the problem might be due to a server issue on Snapchat's end. Check online platforms like Twitter to see if others are reporting similar issues.\n\n10. **Contact Snapchat Support**:\n    - If none of the above solutions work, you might need to reach out to Snapchat Support for further assistance.\n\nTrying these steps should help you open the video. If it's a persistent issue, contacting Snapchat might be necessary to resolve the problem.",
